# Figma-to-Code Workflow

## Required Flow (do not skip)

1. Run `get_design_context` first to fetch the structured representation for the exact Figma node(s)
2. If the response is too large or truncated, run `get_metadata` for the high-level node map, then re-fetch only the required node(s)
3. Run `get_screenshot` for a visual reference of the node variant being implemented
4. Only after you have both design context and screenshot, download any needed assets and start implementation
5. Translate the output (React + Tailwind) into Liquid + CSS following Nootropix conventions
6. Validate against the Figma screenshot for 1:1 visual parity before marking complete

## Translation Rules

IMPORTANT: Figma MCP returns React + Tailwind — this must be translated to Liquid templates + CSS custom properties.

### Colors
- Map all Figma colors to `--color-*` CSS variables from the theme's color adapter
- Never hardcode hex values — use `rgba(var(--color-*))` or `color-mix()`
- If a Figma color has no matching token, check all 6 color schemes before creating a new one

### Typography
- Map Figma text to the heading scale (`--font-heading-*-scale`) or body vars
- Use Inter font family — do not introduce new fonts
- Apply tight negative `letter-spacing` on headings as the theme does

### Spacing
- Map Figma spacing to grid gap vars (`--grid-desktop-*-spacing`) or `--page-gap`
- Use section padding vars (`--pt_dt`, `--pb_dt`, `--pt_mb`, `--pb_mb`) for vertical rhythm
- Container width: `--page-width` (1600px max)

### Border Radius
- Map Figma corner radius to `--*-radius` tokens from `radius-variable-adapter`
- Buttons: `--button-radius: 10rem` (pill)
- Cards: `--product-card-radius: 2.8rem`, `--collection-card-radius: 2rem`
- General: `--general-radius-1` (10px), `--general-radius-2` (15px), `--general-radius-3` (20px), `--general-radius-4` (6px)

### Layout
- Use `<xo-container>` for page-width containers
- Use `<xo-grid>` with `--lg`, `--md`, `--xs` column vars for grids
- Use `xo-stack` with `--ai`, `--jc`, `--gap`, `--dir` for flex layouts
- Use `<xo-animate>` for scroll-triggered entrance animations

### Components
IMPORTANT: Reuse existing snippets before creating new ones:

| Need | Use |
|------|-----|
| Buttons | `{% render 'button' %}` or `{% render 'button-icon' %}` |
| Icons | `{% render 'icon', name: '...', size: '...', color: '...' %}` |
| Images | `{% render 'image' %}` or `{% render 'product-image' %}` |
| Pricing | `{% render 'price' %}` |
| Badges | `{% render 'badge-sale' %}`, `{% render 'badge-new' %}`, `{% render 'badge-sold-out' %}` |
| Headings | `{% render 'section-heading' %}` |
| Collapse | `<xo-collapse>` + `<xo-collapse-trigger>` |
| Carousel | `<xo-carousel>` with sub-components |
| Modal | `<xo-modal>` + `<xo-modal-trigger>` |
| Tabs | `<xo-tabs>` + sub-components |
| Tooltips | `<xo-tooltip>` |

## Component Placement

| Type | Location | Naming |
|------|----------|--------|
| New sections | `sections/{name}.liquid` | Descriptive, lowercase, hyphenated |
| New reusable partials | `snippets/{name}.liquid` | Descriptive, lowercase, hyphenated |
| New cross-section blocks | `blocks/{name}.liquid` | With `{% schema %}` and `{% doc %}` tags |
| Section CSS | `assets/section-{name}.css` | Matches section filename |

## Section Boilerplate

New sections must follow this structure:

```liquid
{{ 'section-{name}.css' | asset_url | stylesheet_tag }}

<section {% render 'section-attr', section: section %}>
  <xo-container>
    {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
      {%- case block.type -%}
        {%- when '@app' -%}
          {% render block %}
        {%- when 'heading' -%}
          ...
      {%- endcase -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  </xo-container>
</section>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Section Name",
  "settings": [...],
  "blocks": [
    { "type": "@theme" },
    { "type": "@app" }
  ],
  "presets": [
    { "name": "Section Name" }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
```

## Asset Handling

- IMPORTANT: If the Figma MCP server returns a localhost source for an image or SVG, use that source directly
- IMPORTANT: DO NOT import or add new icon packages — all icons are inline SVG snippets
- IMPORTANT: DO NOT use or create placeholders if a localhost source is provided
- Store downloaded image assets in `assets/`
- New icons: create `snippets/icon-{name}.liquid` and register the name in `snippets/icon.liquid`

## Accessibility Checklist (per component)

Before marking a Figma implementation as complete, verify:

- [ ] All images have `alt` attributes
- [ ] Interactive elements have `aria-label` where text isn't visible
- [ ] Buttons use `<button>` or `<a>`, not `<div>` with click handlers
- [ ] Color contrast passes 4.5:1 for body text, 3:1 for large text
- [ ] Touch targets are at least 24x24 CSS pixels
- [ ] Focus order matches visual layout order
- [ ] Animations respect `prefers-reduced-motion`
